{"active_answer": "The traffic light system (TLS)", "active_index": 242, "active_question": "What is the name of the most commonly used set of safewords?", "audit_index": 19, "decision": "edit", "document_sha256": "a340552056bb634ce71b5fcef16f1b7d8c00467c32203c06dc7da8d16c6d8d18", "edited_answer": "Red means stop immediately and check the partner’s status; yellow means slow down and be careful; green means everyone is okay to start.", "edited_question": "What do red, yellow, and green mean in the traffic-light safeword system?", "fact_id": "fact-452f36d13d2af7da6837", "prior_review": {"decision": "keep", "path": "data/manual_reviews/context_merit_audit_v17/context_merit_audit_v17.jsonl", "sha256": "4d4fbe2ad209ed6cc927099977de7e88cab3cfb6579baa9512004e1b8b4f49bf", "version": 17}, "reason": "The edit replaces a framework-name lookup with the operational meaning of all three signals.", "reason_code": "replace_safeword_name_with_operational_meanings", "review_pass": "secondary_prior_keep_reaudit", "reviewed_at": "2026-07-14", "reviewer": "codex-context-merit-audit-v29", "risk_features": {"answer_tokens": 5, "bare_answer_points": 0, "named_person_trivia_points": 0, "pronoun_count": 0, "question_tokens": 12, "risk_score": 0, "short_question_points": 0}, "schema": "context-merit-audit-v29", "source": "wikipedia", "source_document": "data/raw/wikipedia_2151448295a2af9b.json", "source_document_file_sha256": "7f17a36cd77f7550f27cb2577f08ca1d880ca30ed72fb029923a62808816cc04", "source_support": "source_composite", "support_evidence": "The traffic light system (TLS) is the most commonly used set of safewords.\n\nRed – meaning: stop immediately and check the status of your partner\nYellow – meaning: slow down, be careful\nGreen – meaning: I'm all good, we can start. If used it's normally uttered by everyone involved before the scene can start.", "support_evidence_sha256": "6e26795889543a7897b02eda58bb05c1b2a4f16ef183a66c3935c13c3041c2b9", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BDSM"}
