{"active_answer": "the basic building block of shibari", "active_index": 251, "active_question": "What is the single column tie described as in relation to shibari?", "audit_index": 24, "decision": "drop", "document_sha256": "130d5aa67e5fe6d28452cd22d1faf78159c8cecce13c6d2e28d499eb0d08b2b4", "fact_id": "fact-a6e93ed860c45d0b353d", "prior_review": {"decision": "keep", "path": "data/manual_reviews/context_merit_audit_v18/context_merit_audit_v18.jsonl", "sha256": "8017b8fac5894878bb1f3395a882672a4d592ddced5fd1e6839bf47f5508bf42", "version": 18}, "reason": "This generic foundation claim comes from a tutorial promotion, while v28 already retained the same source's more useful explanation of why the opening tie matters.", "reason_code": "duplicate_promotional_foundation_claim", "review_pass": "secondary_prior_keep_reaudit", "reviewed_at": "2026-07-14", "reviewer": "codex-context-merit-audit-v29", "risk_features": {"answer_tokens": 6, "bare_answer_points": 0, "named_person_trivia_points": 0, "pronoun_count": 0, "question_tokens": 12, "risk_score": 0, "short_question_points": 0}, "schema": "context-merit-audit-v29", "source": "esinem", "source_document": "data/raw/esinem_64c4212a11867d61.json", "source_document_file_sha256": "ad198e52bd3f3b1ac64a70345c366ffe27ef714bb70a470f93af5fbaaf56c076", "source_support": "normalized_extractive", "support_evidence": "The single column tie is the basic building block of shibari and seems very simple. However, there are many ways to get it wrong and quite a few tricks to getting it right with optimum efficiency.", "support_evidence_sha256": "2848d7d4789d8403b7e68efbcb825ae8b2b256982379853ace6beb797b23d111", "url": "https://www.esinem.com/free-10-pro-tips-for-the-single-column-tie/"}
{"active_answer": "loops getting caught in each other", "active_index": 248, "active_question": "What is the primary cause of rope tangles according to the text?", "audit_index": 25, "decision": "edit", "document_sha256": "f78e9432711b63d7641695edbfc171b7b035f7d4037001f0ff5a5b3c7c3f5541", "edited_answer": "the method of flicking the rope usually does the trick", "edited_question": "What does Esinem say usually works for a rope tangle encountered while tying?", "fact_id": "fact-d7f5bb80b07cc9a258da", "prior_review": {"decision": "keep", "path": "data/manual_reviews/context_merit_audit_v18/context_merit_audit_v18.jsonl", "sha256": "8017b8fac5894878bb1f3395a882672a4d592ddced5fd1e6839bf47f5508bf42", "version": 18}, "reason": "The edit replaces recall of a tangle's cause with the source's concise, directly actionable remedy for a tangle encountered while tying.", "reason_code": "replace_tangle_cause_with_practical_remedy", "review_pass": "secondary_prior_keep_reaudit", "reviewed_at": "2026-07-14", "reviewer": "codex-context-merit-audit-v29", "risk_features": {"answer_tokens": 6, "bare_answer_points": 0, "named_person_trivia_points": 0, "pronoun_count": 0, "question_tokens": 12, "risk_score": 0, "short_question_points": 0}, "schema": "context-merit-audit-v29", "source": "esinem", "source_document": "data/raw/esinem_b249eddc1f5e1864.json", "source_document_file_sha256": "3d300d99942f0b488732ed8136b122dce33504335a1bf89da5ddc5597ef1b26c", "source_support": "normalized_extractive", "support_evidence": "One thing handling a lot of rope, be it tying or preparing orders, has taught us is how to deal with tangles. Believe me, the tangles you get when tying are nothing compared to those we get with a few hundred metres of freshly dried rope when we are treating it. The thing to remember is that rope tangles rarely involve knots; they are usually the result of loops getting caught in each other. This is why the method of lightly tossing the rope about, whilst pulling the tangle apart, works. With the tangles you get when tying, it’s even easier as the method of flicking the rope usually does the trick. Try it, you might be surprised.", "support_evidence_sha256": "a01995899641993def5f22ac09c88f39545f2a513a7cc64cadb26881000128b5", "url": "https://www.esinem.com/untangling-shibari-rope-and-fixing-other-problems/"}
